 as they try to reconcile ideals regarding what it means to be a good parent, a good worker, and a good spouse. Though there are also moments of connection, affection, and care, it’s evident that life for 21st century working parents is frenetic, with extended work hours, children’s activities, chores, meals to prepare, errands to run, and bills to pay.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMiddle class familieszUnited States. 0aMiddle-class familieszUnited States. 0aWork and familyzUnited States. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh1 aArnold, Jeanne E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeck, Margaret, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBradbury, Thomas N., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCampos, Belinda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGarro, Linda C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoodwin, Charles, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGraesch, Anthony P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGutiérrez, Kris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHarness Goodwin, Marjorie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIzquierdo, Carolina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKlein, Wendy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKremer-Sadlik, Tamar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKremer-Sadlik, Tamar, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aOchs, Elinor, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOchs, Elinor, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators